<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-05-15T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-05-15T21:00:00-05:00" n="138" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d138">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/7902: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Peck</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-05-16T10:00:00+08:00">May 16, 1936—10
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received May 16—7 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>140. 1. A responsible official of the Foreign Office has confirmed to an
                            officer of the Embassy a Central News Agency report dated May 15 to
                            effect that Foreign Office on April 7th made oral representations to
                            Japanese Embassy here against increase in Japanese Garrison at Tientsin
                            and that yesterday the Foreign Office instructed Chinese Embassy in
                            Tokyo to make further oral representations in the matter.</p>
                        <p>2. To Department and Peiping. By mail to Tokyo.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Peck</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>